canonical:
  title: 남곤의 자
  author: 朴誾
  language: lzh
  text: 此心無處與深論知我濠梁獨有君談罷歸來乘小雨翠軒牢落一鑪熏
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 남곤의 자
  author: 朴誾
  language: lzh
  text: 此心無處與深論。知我濠梁獨有君。談罷歸來乘小雨。翠軒牢落一鑪熏。
korean:
  title: 사화
  author: 박은
  language: kor
  text: |-
    이 마음을 깊이 논할 곳 없어
    호수 다리 내 마음 알아줄 이 그대뿐이로다
    얘기 끝내고 부슬비를 무릅쓰고 돌아오니
    푸른 마루 뇌락했는데 화로가 다사롭네
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1460_010_0480&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: To a Friend
  author: Park Eun
  language: eng
  text: |-
    This heart finds no one to speak with in depth—
    Only you at the bridge over still waters understand me.
    Our talk done, I return through the gentle rain,
    And in the emerald hall, now lonely and bare,
    Smoke curls from the incense burner, tending to my solitude.
  footnotes:
    - The 'bridge over still waters' (濠梁) alludes to the famous philosophical dialogue between Confucius and Zhuangzi, suggesting a meeting of kindred spirits
    - The incense burner's smoke serves as a meditation on the lingering warmth of friendship after departure
